<br>
We don't need track, and it really wouldn't make any sort of RP sense for us to get it. Tracking is a matter of lore and training. Neither of which our class has inherited. We aren't protectors of the animals. We're not in touch with animals at all beyond the spiritual aspect. This is highlighted by our spell lines as well. We have no charm or fear type spells for animals like a tracking class would have.<br>
<br>
Tracking is a forensic study of animal and terrain. If you've ever seen a real tracker you'll understand this. This fits very well with the RP aspects of druids and rangers. They are dedicated to Nature in the physical aspect. Tunare wants them to protect the plants and animals, so they do. Unless someone tampers with the *spiritual* balance of the world a BST could care less. <p>See me at: <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=47953">Schezarine's Sexay Stuff</a>
